HEADWORD: Telegraphone
<hw>Te*leg"ra*phone</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>th^le</grk> far + <ets>-graph</ets> + <?/ sound.]</ety> <def>An
instrument for recording and reproducing sound by local magnetization of
a steel wire, disk, or ribbon, moved against the pole of a magnet
connected electrically with a telephone receiver, or the like.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

